Class NonConformantDataException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.exception.MaskingException
          • com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.exception.NonConformantDataException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PostMaskTypeConversionException, PreMaskTypeConversionException

    public class NonConformantDataException
extends MaskingException
    Algorithms should throw this exception whenever a value to be masked does not match the expected format. Throwing this exception causes the appropriate non-conformant data handling action to be taken by the masking engine.
    See Also:
